    oneSentenceSummary: "Indiana University is the most underestimated Big Ten school in America — the Kelley School of Business sends more graduates per capita to Chicago financial services than any non-Ivy except Michigan Ross, the Jacobs School of Music is top-3 in the country, and Bloomington is the most beautiful college town in the Midwest, all wrapped in a university that most families outside Indiana still haven't fully discovered.",

    pipeline: "Finance and Investment Banking, Consulting, Technology, Media and Journalism, Music Performance and Music Business, Law, Education, Healthcare, Data Science. Kelley School of Business sends graduates to Goldman Sachs, J.P. Morgan, Deloitte, PwC, and all Big 4 accounting firms at rates that rival Michigan Ross per capita. The Jacobs School of Music is consistently ranked top-3 nationally alongside Juilliard and Eastman. The Media School produces national journalists, sports media personalities, and digital content leaders. The Maurer School of Law feeds federal clerkships and Big Law firms in Chicago and New York. IU's cybersecurity and data science programs have grown significantly in placement depth. 33,000 undergraduates; 98% first-to-second year retention.",

    hiddenPathway: "The Kelley School of Business is the most consequential hidden asset in Indiana University's profile — and one of the most underestimated undergraduate business programs in the country. Kelley sends more graduates to the Chicago financial services sector per capita than any non-Ivy school except Michigan Ross. The IBP (Integrated Business and Pre-Law) and LAMP (Liberal Arts and Management) programs are nationally distinctive dual-track programs that no peer institution replicates. The Wells Scholars Program is one of the most generous merit scholarship programs at any public university in America — full tuition plus stipend — and its alumni network includes CEOs, senators, and MacArthur Fellows. Kelley's Investment Banking Workshop is among the most rigorous undergraduate finance preparation programs in the country outside of Wharton.",

    institutionalSecret: "Indiana University is a legitimate top-20 public university whose national reputation lags behind its actual placement outcomes by approximately ten years. Families who dismiss IU as a regional school are making a material error — particularly in finance, music, media, and data science, where IU's outcomes rival institutions with significantly higher name recognition. The Bloomington campus is also one of the most architecturally beautiful in the country, which matters more than people admit when a student is deciding where to spend four years.",

    theRoom: "1,900-acre campus in Bloomington — a city of 80,000 built almost entirely around the university. 49% of students are Indiana residents and 51% are from out of state or international, a ratio consistent for three years that reflects IU's deliberate national recruitment push. The campus is defined by limestone Gothic architecture, the Showalter Fountain, the Sample Gates, and the Jordan River running through the center. Big Ten athletics, Greek life (one of the largest systems in the country), and Bloomington's independent music and restaurant culture create a social environment that is genuinely exceptional for a Midwestern public university.",

    lifestyle: "Bloomington is the quintessential college town — IU is the entire economy, culture, and social infrastructure. Kirkwood Avenue, the Sample Gates, the Lilly Library, and Assembly Hall define a campus geography that students navigate on foot and bicycle year-round. The winters are cold but manageable. The Little 500 bike race — made famous by the film Breaking Away — is the defining annual event, a genuinely beloved campus tradition that attracts national attention.",

    bestFitPersonality: "High Conscientiousness (Kelley-track), High Extraversion, Comfortable in large social environments, Drawn to Midwest pragmatism, Finance or business-oriented, Music-passionate (Jacobs track), Midwestern community-oriented",

    faithTradition: "Nonsectarian Public University",

    geographicInfluenceRadius: "Midwest dominant — Chicago financial services primary, Indianapolis corporate market, national through Kelley and Jacobs alumni networks",

    economicOutcome: "Exceptional outcomes in finance and investment banking through Kelley; top-3 music performance outcomes through Jacobs; strong journalism and media placement through the Media School; growing technology and data science pipelines",

