    theRoom: "2,400 students on a 95-acre campus 25 miles west of Chicago. Every student signs a community covenant — no alcohol, no tobacco — which functions as a self-selection mechanism producing a campus where students are genuinely aligned in values. The academic culture is demanding and intellectually serious by evangelical standards; Wheaton is sometimes called the Harvard of Christian colleges, which understates both institutions. Division III athletics, strong music and arts programs, and a residential culture built around small communities of serious people.",

