    oneSentenceSummary: "Seattle Pacific University is a Free Methodist liberal arts university of 3,800 students in the Queen Anne neighborhood of Seattle — combining a rigorous Christian academic tradition with direct access to one of America's most consequential technology and social impact ecosystems.",

    pipeline: "Business and Economics — SPU's School of Business and Economics places graduates into Amazon, Microsoft, Boeing, Starbucks, and the Seattle nonprofit sector. Education — SPU's School of Education is one of the most respected teacher preparation programs in Washington State. Nursing — top-ranked in Washington, feeding Swedish Medical Center, UW Medicine, and Seattle Children's Hospital. Psychology and Counseling — SPU produces a disproportionate share of Pacific Northwest licensed counselors and social workers. Computer Science and Engineering — growing placement in the Seattle technology corridor. 3,800 undergraduates; 4,200 total enrollment.",

    hiddenPathway: "Seattle Pacific's most consequential hidden asset is its Queen Anne location — a residential neighborhood adjacent to South Lake Union, Amazon's global headquarters campus, and the most concentrated technology workforce in America outside of Silicon Valley. An SPU nursing, business, or computer science graduate in Seattle is 15 minutes from Amazon, Microsoft's Seattle offices, and the entire South Lake Union technology corridor. The SPU Honors Program is one of the most rigorous undergraduate great books programs at any evangelical university in America — producing graduates who go on to law school, doctoral programs, and public policy careers at rates that significantly exceed institutional size.",

    institutionalSecret: "SPU's integration of Christian faith and rigorous academic culture within one of America's most progressive and economically dynamic cities creates a distinctive student experience that no peer institution replicates. Students can engage the full intellectual and professional life of Seattle while being rooted in a tight-knit Christian community of 3,800. The tension between SPU's faith tradition and Seattle's progressive culture is not a weakness — it is the defining character-forming pressure of four years there.",

    theRoom: "Queen Anne is one of Seattle's most desirable residential neighborhoods — a hill overlooking Puget Sound, the Space Needle, and the downtown skyline. The campus of 35 acres is intimate by design. 70% of students live on campus. The student body draws primarily from the Pacific Northwest and California, with a significant international student population from Asia. The Free Methodist faith tradition is present but not imposing — students of many faith backgrounds attend.",

    lifestyle: "Seattle is one of the most culturally rich, economically dynamic, and physically beautiful cities in America. Four years at SPU is four years in a city that is simultaneously a technology capital, a coffee culture landmark, an outdoor recreation hub, and one of the most progressive civic environments in the country. Pike Place Market, Capitol Hill, the waterfront, and the Cascades are all accessible.",

    bestFitPersonality: "High Conscientiousness, Faith-motivated, Service-oriented, Comfortable in progressive urban environments, Pacific Northwest-drawn, Nursing or education or technology-oriented",

