    pipeline: "Liberal Arts and Sciences across all disciplines. Business Economics — top placement track into Los Angeles and San Francisco financial services and consulting. Communication Studies — producing journalists, public relations professionals, and media leaders. Kinesiology — top pre-physical therapy and pre-medical track. Education — credentialing into California's public and private school systems. Political Science and Pre-Law — strong law school placement record. 1,300 undergraduates only.",

    hiddenPathway: "Westmont's location above Santa Barbara — one of the most beautiful and expensive communities in California — is both an asset and an identity. Students on Westmont's 111-acre campus are living in a physical environment that rivals any college in the country. The Westmont in San Francisco program and the Westmont in Europe program give students access to immersive urban and international experiences within the Westmont framework. The college's size means that every student who wants undergraduate research, faculty mentorship, or leadership opportunity can have it — something that is structurally impossible at peer institutions ten times larger.",

    institutionalSecret: "Westmont produces law school, graduate school, and professional program admissions at rates that significantly exceed what its name recognition would predict. The combination of rigorous liberal arts curriculum, small class sizes averaging 18 students, and deep faculty mentorship creates an undergraduate preparation that selective graduate programs have learned to trust. Westmont graduates regularly gain admission to UC law schools, seminary doctoral programs, and competitive fellowship programs alongside graduates of much more prominent institutions.",

    theRoom: "111-acre campus in Montecito, directly above Santa Barbara. 1,300 students — one of the smallest residential liberal arts colleges on the West Coast. 83% of students live on campus. The student body is demographically diverse for an evangelical institution — drawing significantly from California's urban centers, Hawaii, and the Pacific Northwest. The campus overlooks the Pacific and the Channel Islands.",

    lifestyle: "Santa Barbara is one of the most physically beautiful cities in California — a Mediterranean climate, Spanish Colonial architecture, beaches, hiking, and a cultural scene that belies its size. Westmont students have access to the full Santa Barbara lifestyle while living in an intentional Christian academic community. Los Angeles is 90 miles south — accessible for internships, entertainment industry connection, and weekend engagement.",

