    oneSentenceSummary: "Penn State is one of America's most powerful alumni network universities — a comprehensive public flagship where the 750,000-person Nittany Lion network, Smeal College of Business, and engineering programs combine with a campus culture so cohesive it functions as a lifelong professional and social identity.",

    pipeline: "Acceptance rate approximately 54% overall, significantly more selective for Smeal College of Business and engineering. #14 among public universities nationally (US News 2025). 47,000+ students at University Park campus; 90,000+ system-wide. Smeal College of Business is top-20 in supply chain, finance, and accounting. College of Engineering ranks top-15 in aerospace, industrial, and materials engineering. Over 750,000 living alumni — one of the largest alumni networks in the world by absolute count. The Penn State alumni network is distinguished not just by size but by loyalty and referral culture — Penn State alumni hire Penn State graduates at a rate that is structurally embedded into Pennsylvanian and mid-Atlantic business culture.",

    hiddenPathway: "The Penn State Schreyer Honors College is one of the most rigorous and most valuable honors programs at any public university in America — a genuine small-liberal-arts-college experience inside a flagship, with its own residential community, thesis requirement, and alumni network. Schreyer Scholars are among the most recruited students at Penn State, and the Schreyer alumni network operates almost as a separate, elite sub-network within the larger Penn State alumni base. The Supply Chain and Information Systems program within Smeal is consistently ranked #1 nationally — companies like Amazon, Apple, Walmart, and every major logistics firm recruit Penn State supply chain graduates at volume. The Nittany Lion Fund within Smeal is one of the only undergraduate student-managed investment funds at a public university that gives students real capital to manage — a differentiator in finance recruiting.",

    institutionalSecret: "Penn State's 24-campus commonwealth system is a genuine access pathway that most applicants don't optimize. Students who want Penn State credentials but face admissions pressure at University Park can enter through a commonwealth campus — DuBois, Altoona, Behrend, Harrisburg — and transfer to University Park after one or two years. The degree says Penn State. The alumni network is the same. The commonwealth campus pathway is one of the most underutilized access strategies for a flagship of Penn State's caliber.",

    theRoom: "State College, Pennsylvania — a genuine college town built entirely around the university, population 42,000, isolated in the Allegheny Mountains of central Pennsylvania. This isolation is a feature, not a bug: it creates extraordinary campus cohesion, a social life that is entirely on-campus, and a community bond that persists decades after graduation. Philadelphia is 3 hours east, Pittsburgh 2.5 hours west. The Beaver Stadium atmosphere — 107,000 capacity, one of the largest stadiums in the world — is the physical expression of Penn State's communal identity.",

