    location: "New York City, New York, USA",

    region: "Bos-Wash Megalopolis",

    archetype: "The Global Elite Gateway — New York, Power, and the Center of Everything",

    oneSentenceSummary: "Columbia is the only Ivy League university located in New York City — and that single fact makes it categorically different from every peer institution, embedding 9,000 undergraduates directly into the world's financial, media, arts, fashion, and publishing capital from day one of freshman year.",

    pipeline: "3.9% acceptance rate for the Class of 2028. #12 nationally (US News 2025). 9,000 undergraduates across Columbia College and the Fu Foundation School of Engineering. Columbia Law School is top-5 nationally. Columbia Business School is top-10. Columbia Journalism School is the most prestigious journalism graduate program in America — the Pulitzer Prize is administered by Columbia. Wall Street firms are a 30-minute subway ride from campus. Goldman Sachs, JPMorgan, Blackstone, KKR, and every major investment bank and private equity firm have offices within 3 miles of Morningside Heights. NBCUniversal, Condé Nast, The New York Times, HBO, and virtually every major media company recruit Columbia students directly. 320,000+ living alumni.",

    hiddenPathway: "Columbia's Core Curriculum — Literature Humanities, Contemporary Civilization, Art Humanities, Music Humanities, University Writing, Frontiers of Science — is the most famous and most intellectually demanding general education requirement in American higher education. Every Columbia undergraduate reads the same books: Homer, Plato, Thucydides, Dante, Cervantes, Kant, Marx, Woolf. The shared intellectual experience of the Core creates a Columbia identity that is unusually cohesive for a university of this size and urban character. The Core is not a burden at Columbia — it is the point. The Columbia Undergraduate Research Program gives students access to faculty research projects across all disciplines from freshman year. The Manhattanville expansion campus (130th Street) is creating a new research and entrepreneurship zone that is beginning to generate its own Columbia-adjacent startup ecosystem.",

    institutionalSecret: "Columbia's greatest undersurfaced asset is its dual-degree programs. The 3-2 Engineering program allows students at Columbia's affiliated liberal arts colleges to complete three years at their home institution and two years at Columbia's engineering school, earning degrees from both. The Columbia-Sciences Po dual degree, the Columbia-London School of Economics program, and the Columbia Global Centers network give students international academic access that no other Ivy can match at scale. Columbia's location also creates an internship culture that is unparalleled — students regularly complete two or three substantive internships before graduation simply because the companies are there.",

    theRoom: "Morningside Heights, Manhattan — at 116th Street and Broadway, between the Upper West Side and Harlem. The campus is contained, deliberately designed as an urban acropolis above the city grid. Low Plaza, Butler Library, and the iconic steps create a physical center. The subway (1 train) connects campus to Midtown in 20 minutes and the Financial District in 35. Central Park is 10 blocks south. The neighborhoods surrounding Columbia — Harlem, Washington Heights, the Upper West Side — are among the most culturally significant in America.",

    lifestyle: "Intensely urban and intellectually engaged. Columbia students live in New York in a way that students at campus-centered universities do not — internships, cultural events, and professional networking begin immediately and continue throughout the four years. The campus creates a residential core within the urban environment, but the city is always present. The culture is sophisticated, ambitious, and cosmopolitan. Social life extends beyond the campus into New York's restaurant, arts, and nightlife ecosystem in ways that have no equivalent at peer universities.",

    bestFitPersonality: "Urban-oriented, cosmopolitan, intellectually rigorous, finance or media or law or international affairs ambition, comfortable in density and complexity, high Openness and Extraversion",

