    pipeline: "78% acceptance rate for the Class of 2028. #96 among public universities nationally (US News 2025). 22,000 undergraduates. The Missouri School of Journalism is #1 in the world — it invented the field, runs a real daily newspaper (the Columbia Missourian), a real television station (KOMU-TV, the only university-owned commercial NBC affiliate in the US), and a real radio station as instructional labs. The Trulaske College of Business is top-50. The College of Engineering is top-75. The College of Agriculture, Food and Natural Resources is top-20. The Mizzou Health system and School of Medicine create a healthcare pipeline in mid-Missouri. 300,000+ living alumni with strong Missouri and Midwest presence.",

