    institutionalSecret: "Columbia, Missouri is the most genuinely pleasant college city in the Midwest that most people outside Missouri have never visited. The 38th parallel runs through Columbia — Stephens Lake Park, the MKT Nature and Fitness Trail, and the surrounding agricultural landscape create outdoor culture. The craft brewery scene, the downtown District, and the uniquely Missouri food culture (toasted ravioli, gooey butter cake, Missouri wine country) create a lifestyle that Mizzou students describe with genuine enthusiasm. Columbia's position at the intersection of I-70 and US-63 places it equidistant between Kansas City and St. Louis — both metro areas within 2 hours — giving students access to two major Midwest business corridors.",

