    archetype: "The Iowa Writers Workshop University — Healthcare Leadership, Literary Excellence, and the Hawkeye Medical Pipeline",

    oneSentenceSummary: "Iowa is the university that invented creative writing as an academic discipline — the Iowa Writers Workshop has produced more Pulitzer Prize winners, National Book Award recipients, and working literary novelists than any other program in the world — while simultaneously operating one of the top academic medical centers in America and a healthcare research enterprise that defines the career landscape of Iowa City.",

    pipeline: "82% acceptance rate for the Class of 2028. #92 among public universities nationally (US News 2025). 22,000 undergraduates. The Carver College of Medicine is top-30 in research funding. University of Iowa Hospitals and Clinics is one of the top-20 academic medical centers in America. The Tippie College of Business is top-40. The College of Engineering is top-50. The Iowa Writers Workshop — graduate program — is the most prestigious creative writing program in the world, and its influence flows back into undergraduate English and creative writing. The Hawkeye athletic network in wrestling and Big Ten sports creates alumni bonds that extend across the Midwest. 235,000+ living alumni.",

    hiddenPathway: "University of Iowa Hospitals and Clinics is Iowa's most important career pipeline and its least nationally discussed asset. UIHC is the largest hospital in Iowa, one of the top-20 academic medical centers in the country, and the healthcare economic anchor of Iowa City. For pre-med students, the UIHC proximity — walking distance from the main campus — creates shadowing, research, and clinical volunteer access that private university pre-med programs at similar selectivity levels cannot match. The Carver College of Medicine's strong research funding means undergraduate research positions are genuinely available. The National Advanced Driving Simulator (NADS) on campus — the most advanced driving simulation facility in the world — creates a niche engineering and human factors research access that reflects Iowa's commitment to applied federal research.",

    institutionalSecret: "Iowa City is the only city in the United States designated a UNESCO City of Literature — a designation it shares with Edinburgh, Melbourne, and Dublin — reflecting the literary culture that the Iowa Writers Workshop has built into the DNA of the place. The Prairie Lights bookstore, the Wednesday Night Poetry series, and the Iowa Summer Writing Festival create a literary ecosystem that is genuinely unusual for a mid-size Midwest college city. Writers who attended the Workshop — Flannery O'Connor, Raymond Carver, John Irving, Marilynne Robinson, Denis Johnson — have shaped American fiction in the twentieth century more than graduates of any other single program.",

    theRoom: "Iowa City, Iowa — a city of 74,000 on the Iowa River in eastern Iowa, 30 miles from the Quad Cities and 120 miles from Des Moines. The Old Capitol Building — the original territorial and state capitol of Iowa — sits at the top of the Iowa campus as its physical center. The Pedestrian Mall downtown is the commercial and social spine. The Iowa River runs through campus. Iowa City is one of the most walkable and intellectually distinctive college cities in the Midwest — the UNESCO City of Literature designation is not ironic.",

    lifestyle: "Big Ten athletics with a literary and healthcare core. Kinnick Stadium and the Iowa Hawkeye football and wrestling culture provide the social organizing architecture for the broader student body. The Iowa Writers Workshop graduate community creates an intellectual atmosphere that is unusual for a flagship of Iowa's size — undergraduates in English and creative writing benefit from proximity to one of the most accomplished writing communities in the world. Iowa City's bar and restaurant culture along Dubuque Street and the Ped Mall is active and student-centered.",

