    pipeline: "55% acceptance rate for the Class of 2028. #14 among public regional universities in the West (US News 2025). 40,000 undergraduates — one of the largest CSU enrollments. The Mihaylo College of Business and Economics is top-40 nationally in accounting — it produces more licensed CPAs in California than any other university, making it the dominant pipeline into the Big Four offices that serve OC's corporate base. The College of Engineering and Computer Science is top-25 among CSU campuses. The College of Communications is one of the strongest in the CSU system in advertising, public relations, and journalism. Deloitte, KPMG, EY, PwC, Disneyland Resort, Allergan, and every major Orange County corporation recruit CSUF at volume. 300,000+ living alumni concentrated in Orange County and the LA metro.",

