    institutionalSecret: "Orange County is America's most misunderstood economic ecosystem — and CSUF is its primary talent pipeline. OC is not LA's suburb. It is an independent economy of 3.2 million people with its own Fortune 500 companies (Broadcom, Edwards Lifesciences, Allergan, Pacific Life), its own startup ecosystem (the Irvine technology corridor), and its own real estate, healthcare, and hospitality industries. CSUF graduates are embedded in this economy at every level — the density of CSUF alumni in OC corporate, legal, and accounting settings creates the same self-reinforcing professional network that Penn State provides in Pennsylvania, at public CSU cost.",

